France is the most popular ski destination for Brits this winter accounting for a staggering 87 per cent of all enquiries. 

Austria and Switzerland remain popular, although demand for both is down on last year while Andorra has seen a significant hike in popularity with enquiries up 32 per cent on last season. 

Morzine is the number one choice for Brits and demand for this resort is up 16 per cent on last year, in research by Owners Direct. 

