Val Thorens, Meribel and La Plagne have also experienced a big leap in demand versus last season, whereas Chamonix has seen demand fall by 23 per cent and it has dropped from position four to position nine in the 'top 10'. 

'France is the clear winner among British skiers this season,' says Erica Chang, Senior Regional Director, Owners Direct. 

'Demand for ski accommodation in France has risen year-on-year and our top ten ski resorts are all French.'

